---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Agent Practice | Contribute" canonicalPath="/contribute">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="copy-block">
      <div class="section-kicker">Contribute</div>
      <h2>We want contributors to add signal, not noise.</h2>
      <p>
        The easiest good contribution is not “more AI content”. It is a sharper challenge, a better grader, a clearer
        starter template, or tighter docs around the local workflow.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="copy-block">
      <div class="section-kicker">Open-source contract</div>
      <p>Use the repo to add challenge folders, graders, templates, and docs. MVP does not include accounts, cloud submissions, or a hosted leaderboard.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="contribute-grid">
      <article>
        <div class="mono">A</div>
        <h3>Challenge Authors</h3>
        <p>Write a problem statement, fixtures, schemas, and a deterministic grader. Keep the runtime contract stable.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <div class="mono">B</div>
        <h3>Template Maintainers</h3>
        <p>Improve raw Python, LangChain, and LangGraph examples without locking the project to one framework.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <div class="mono">C</div>
        <h3>Evaluator Builders</h3>
        <p>Add regression tests, grading rigor, and future evaluation assets that preserve local reproducibility.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <div class="mono">D</div>
        <h3>UI Contributors</h3>
        <p>Help the static site stay useful, dense, and readable as the catalog and docs expand.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
